cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MED, cs.IR 

This paper deals with the application of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for medical image analysis, specifically for diabetic retinopathy. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of weakly supervised learning, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of CNNs for medical image analysis also falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper deals with medical image analysis, which falls under the category of cs.MED (Medical Imaging). Finally, the paper discusses the use of image-level labels, which can be considered as a form of information retrieval, falling under the category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
